The Wind—tapped like a tired Man—  
And like a Parent—the Water—  
The Quiet Face of Nature—sung  
And danced, to ease their pain—  

The Rain—it clears the development  
Of Life, before the day—  
The Stream—brings White Cornflowers down  
To light the summer fray!

- Emily Dickinson
